3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20feel%20like%20the%20US%20economy%20has%20been%20in%20a%20will-they-won't-they%20phase%20with%20a%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fare-we-in-a-recession%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecession%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20far%20too%20long%2C%20you're%20not%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20dreaded%20R-word%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-we-in-a-recession-now-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooming%20over%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20years%2C%20one%20top%20economist%20said%20this%20week%20that%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20recession%20has%20climbed%20to%2090%25.%20The%20last%20time%20the%20US%20was%20in%20a%20recession%20was%20in%202020%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recession%2C%20or%20a%20significant%20downturn%20in%20economic%20activity%20that%20lasts%20more%20than%20a%20few%20months%2C%20is%20typically%20defined%20as%20two%20consecutive%20quarters%20of%20negative%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%2C%20or%20GDP.%20Negative%20GDP%20means%20the%20total%20value%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20produced%20is%20declining%20%E2%80%94%20in%20other%20words%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20shrinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommon%20recession%20indicators%20include%20a%20decline%20in%20GDP%2C%20a%20decline%20in%20real%20income%2C%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20unemployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20said%20China%20faces%20tariffs%20of%20up%20to%20245%25%2C%20and%20his%20administration%20has%20also%20imposed%20a%20widely%20applied%2010%25%20tariff.%20The%20announcements%20have%20fueled%20new%20concerns%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20with%20economists%20warning%20about%20the%20potential%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20first-quarter%20survey%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Fbanking%2Ffederal-reserve%2Feconomic-indicator-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBankrate%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20top%20economists%20believed%20a%20recession%20was%20becoming%C2%A0more%20likely.%20The%20survey%20found%20the%20odds%20of%20a%20recession%20occurring%20in%20the%20next%2012%20months%20was%2036%25%2C%20up%20from%2026%25%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202024%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20was%20before%20Trump%20ramped%20up%20his%20trade%20war%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20leading%20economists%20have%20said%20lately%20about%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2258fd5a33-5c5c-44cf-b221-2a14324f7370%5C%22%3ETorsten%20Sl%C3%B8k%2C%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETorsten%20Sl%C3%B8k%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-2025-outlook-economy-downturn-trump-tariffs-china-small-business-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%20economist%20at%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20asset-management%20firm%20based%20in%20New%20York.%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said%20in%20a%20note%20to%20Apollo%20clients%20over%20the%20weekend%20that%20there%20was%20now%20a%2090%25%20chance%20of%20the%20US%20entering%20into%20a%20%26quot%3BVoluntary%20Trade%20Reset%20Recession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariffs%20have%20been%20implemented%20in%20a%20way%20that%20has%20not%20been%20effective%2C%26quot%3B%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said.%20%26quot%3BSmall%20businesses%20that%20have%20for%20decades%20relied%20on%20a%20stable%20US%20system%20will%20have%20to%20adjust%20immediately%20and%20do%20not%20have%20the%20working%20capital%20to%20pay%20tariffs.%20Expect%20ships%20to%20sit%20offshore%2C%20orders%20to%20be%20canceled%2C%20and%20well-run%20generational%20retailers%20to%20file%20for%20bankruptcy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESl%C3%B8k%20gave%20several%20reasons%20why%20a%20downturn%20for%20small%20businesses%20could%20have%20a%20large%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20including%20that%20they%20account%20for%20most%20American%20jobs%20and%20more