nomist%20and%20former%20president%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%2C%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20stagflation%20could%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest-case%20scenario%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20op-ed%20for%20Bloomberg%2C%20Dudley%20said%20the%20White%20House's%20tariff%20policy%20could%20lead%20to%205%25%20inflation%20in%20the%20next%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20companies%20pass%20along%20the%20cost%20of%20higher%20imports%20to%20consumers%2C%20inflation%20will%20be%20more%20persistent%20and%20the%20Fed%20less%20friendly.%20If%20they%20can't%2C%20profit%20margins%20will%20shrink%20and%20earnings%20will%20underwhelm%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20told%2C%20stagflation%20is%20the%20optimistic%20scenario.%20More%20likely%2C%20the%20US%20will%20end%20up%20in%20a%20full-blown%20recession%20accompanied%20by%20higher%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286c1a061-4384-4791-81cb-0befb9894a3e%5C%22%3EBruce%20Kasman%2C%20J.P.%20Morgan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJ.P.%20Morgan%20said%20in%20a%20note%20last%20week%20that%20the%20bank%20believes%20the%20likelihood%20of%20the%20US%20entering%20a%20recession%20in%202025%20was%2060%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20with%20the%20latest%20step-back%20from%20the%20draconian%20Liberation%20Day%20measures%2C%20what%20remains%20is%20still%20enough%20to%20push%20the%20US%20and%20China%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20likely%20the%20global%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20into%20a%20recession%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Bruce%20Kasman%2C%20chief%20global%20economist%20at%20J.P.%20Morgan%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20note%20said%20the%20high%20tariff%20on%20China%20alongside%20the%20universal%2010%25%20tariff%20increased%20the%20average%20US%20tariff%20rate%20to%2030%25%20and%20that%20it%20amounted%20to%20%241%20trillion%2C%20or%203%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20it%20the%20largest%20tax%20increase%20on%20US%20households%20and%20businesses%20since%20World%20War%20II.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20remains%20is%20still%20enough%20to%20push%20the%20US%20and%20China%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20likely%20the%20global%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20into%20a%20recession%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Kasman%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BAnother%20important%20concern%20is%20that%20sustained%20restrictive%20trade%20policies%20and%20reduced%20immigration%20flow%20may%20impose%20lasting%20supply%20costs%2C%20which%20will%20lower%20US%20growth%20over%20the%20long%20run.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f05f33b7-36d2-417b-8b3e-b71a89e45f0f%5C%22%3EBut%20the%20US%20could%20still%20avoid%20a%20recession%2C%20some%20say%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStrategists%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-prediction-us-economy-downturn-trump-tariffs-inflation-wealth-2025-2025-4%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWells%20Fargo%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%20there%20were%20some%20key%20signs%20that%20the%20US%20could%20avoid%20a%20recession%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20bank%20lowered%20its%20GDP%20growth%20expectations%2C%20it%20said%20some%20economic%20pullback%20could%20be%20a%20correction%20from%20a%20strong%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKey%20economic%20supports%20remain%20intact%2C%20in%20our%20view%2C%20and%20can%20limit%20the%20slowdown%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20fertile%20ground%20for%20a%20moderate%20second-half%20growth%20recovery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20positive%20signs%20included%20steady%20income%20growth%2C%20an%20increase%20in%20household%20wealth%2C%20long-term%20interest%20rates%20being%20down%2C%20and%20that%20financial%20markets%20remain%20liquid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-trump-tariff-trade-war-economy-outlook-stoltzfus-2025-4%3Futm_sourc