20to%202022%20reveal%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Facebook%20struggled%20to%20coexist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20emails%2C%20Zuckerberg%20expressed%20concerns%20that%20the%20photo-sharing%20app%20had%20begun%20to%20%26quot%3Bcannibalize%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Zuckerberg's%20POV%2C%20Facebook%20was%20driving%20Instagram's%20growth%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20engagement%20and%20its%20own%20relevance%2C%20and%20it%20was%20time%20for%20Instagram%20to%20return%20the%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20he%20also%20emphasized%20that%20he%20wanted%20Instagram%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20growing%2C%20even%20understanding%20it%20will%20naturally%20cannibalize%20FB%20somewhat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20clearly%20a%20tricky%20situation%20for%20Zuckerberg%20to%20navigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOut-of-context%20and%20years-old%20documents%20about%20acquisitions%20that%20were%20reviewed%20by%20the%20FTC%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%20will%20not%20obscure%20the%20realities%20of%20the%20competition%20we%20face%20or%20overcome%20the%20FTC's%20weak%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Meta%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2293e6b7f4-893f-4f97-b7a6-dcceb33359d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EZuck's%20big%20regret%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20documents%20from%202018%20show%20a%20recurring%20topic%20of%20concern%3A%20Instagram%20overshadowing%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Facebook%20app%20has%20historically%20driven%20most%20of%20Instagram's%20growth%20through%20bookmarks%20and%20other%20links%2C%20and%20has%20born%20a%20higher%20ad%20load%20tax%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20board%20members%20in%202018.%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20contributed%20to%20a%20headwind%20for%20Facebook%20in%20that%20it%20sends%20some%20of%20its%20engagement%20to%20Instagram.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67896bc810c98eace912bed1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20struggled%20with%20how%20to%20grow%20both%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook.%3Cp%3EManuel%20Orbegozo%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202018%2C%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20to%20several%20Facebook%20executives%20in%20an%20email%20that%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20major%20mistakes%20I%20regret%20is%20not%20reducing%20the%20massive%20inorganic%20distribution%20to%20Instagram%20sooner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20had%20stopped%20aggressively%20promoting%20Instagram%20at%20500%20million%20people%2C%20for%20example%20it%20would%20have%20had%20sufficient%20scale%20to%20build%20and%20compete%20on%20Stories%20and%20we%20would%20not%20have%20the%20same%20concern%20about%20network%20fragmentation%20that%20we%20have%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20email%2C%20Zuckerberg%20posed%20the%20question%3A%20Is%20Instagram%20%26quot%3Bjust%20a%20better%20product%26quot%3B%20than%20Facebook%3F%20Zuck%20didn't%20think%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20our%20metrics%20suggests%20that%20Instagram%20is%20a%20good%20but%20overall%20less%20effective%20product%2C%20and%20is%20likely%20only%20growing%20so%20quickly%20because%20we%20promoted%20it%20heavily%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2282c140f7-02e2-4d64-930e-e2916bee91b3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstagram%20had%20become%20the%20cooler%2C%20younger%20sibling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFacebook%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20needed%20to%20maintain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facebook-losing-cultural-relevancy-mark-zuckerberg-emails-ftc-trial-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelevance%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20its%20users%20as%20Instagram%20grew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20an%20Amazon%20Echo%20and%20start%20using%20it%20after%20you%20already%20use%20Amazon%20for%20commerce%2C%20you%20feel%20like%20Amazon%20is%20getting%20more%20relevant%20in%20your%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20the%20May%202018%20email%20to%20executives.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20when%20you%20get%20Instagram%20and%20start%20using%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20Facebook%20you%20feel%20like%20Facebook%20as%20a%20company%20is%20getting%20less%20relevant%20in%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20saw%20two%20options%20for%20improving%20Facebook's%20relevance%20at%20the%20time%3A%20double%20down%20on%20Facebook's%20branding%20when%20users%20opened%20Instagram%20and%20WhatsApp%2C%20or%20change%20the%20corporate%20brand%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20did%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D2e84ec069f8c9621d7404e7cb55bf445b3d31315699ebf40d2e714edaa58715c%26postID%3D6802b130b154b4859e788fb5%26postSlug%3Dmark-zuckerberg-tried-control-instagram-and-facebook-sibling-rivalry-2025-4%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theinformation.com%252Farticles%252Ffacebook-to-add-its-name-to-instagram-whatsapp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20%26quot%3BInstagram%20from%20Facebook%26quot%3B%20tagline.%20Then%2C%20in%202021%2C%20Facebook%20changed%20its%20corporate%20name%20to%20Meta%20Platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%202022%2C%20and%20Facebook's%20relevance%20in%20users'%20lives%20was%20still%20a%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%20IG%20is%20doing%20well%20on%20cultural%20relevance%20and%20FB%20isn't%2C%20so%20I'm%20more%20focused%20on%20figuring%20out%20a%20reasonable%20path%20for%20FB%20longer%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20head%20of%20Facebook%20Tom%20Alison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eee20f59-1de4-4094-9594-57a826a6cfef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrying%20to%20reel%20in%20Instagram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%202018%2C%20Zuckerberg%20discussed%20several%20options%20that%20could%20help%20preserve%20Facebook's%20cultural%20relevance%20and%20growth%20amid%20Instagram's%20%26quot%3Bcannibalization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20that%20were%20discussed%20in%20the%20court%20documents%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPromoting%20Instagram%20less%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20our%20concern%20about%20these%20effects%2C%20we%20have%20reduced%20our%20promotions%20from%20Facebook%20to%20Instagram%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20to%20executives%20in%20May%202018.%20%26quot%3BThese%20remain%20significant%20levers%20for%20changing%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20future%20growth%20of%20the%20family%2C%20and%20as%20painful%20as%20it%20would%20be%20to%20reduce%20Instagram%20growth%20and%20revenue%20forecasts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20manage%20the%20team%20through%20this%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20rational%20to%20pull%20these%20levers%20to%20effectively%20zero%20until%20we%20reach%20a%20reasonable%20balance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EReducing%20Facebook's%20ad%20load.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%26quot%3BThere's%20absolutely%20no%20reason%20why%20IG%20ad%20load%20should%20be%20lower%20than%20FB%20at%20a%20time%20when%20%E2%80%A6%20we're%20having%20engagement%20issues%20in%20FB%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20a%20January%202018%20email%20thread%20with%20executives.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20were%20managing%20our%20company%20correctly%2C%20then%20at%20a%20minimum%20we'd%20immediately%20balance%20IG%20and%20FB%20ad%20load%20%E2%80%94%20this%20week%20or%20this%20month%2C%20not%20this%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpinning%20out%20Instagram%20was%20even%20floated%20as%20an%20option%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Zuckerberg%20wondered%20if%20Facebook%20%26quot%3Bshould%20consider%20the%20extreme%20step%20of%20spinning%20Instagram%20out%20as%20a%20separate%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20May%202018%20email%20to%20executives.%20%26quot%3BI%20understand%20the%20business%20value%20of%20having%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%20together%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20raise%20this%20lightly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanging%20up%20internal%20leadership%20with%20a%20reorg.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%202018%2C%20there%20was%20a%20shake-up%20across%20the%20company.%20Chris%20Cox%20was%20appointed%20to%20oversee%20product%20across%20the%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20of%20apps%20%E2%80%94%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20Messenger%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Adam%20Mosseri%20was%20moved%20from%20Facebook%20to%20Instagram%20as%20VP%20of%20product.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20we're%20trying%20a%20new%20org%20structure%20is%20because%20the%20status%20quo%20isn't%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20apps%20are%20neither%20operating%20independently%20nor%20with%20a%20rational%20value%20exchange%20today.%20Instead%2C%20we%20are%20siphoning%20off%20the%20network%20from%20the%20Facebook%20app%20to%20artificially%20grow%20Instagram%20and%20Messenger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDifferentiating%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Zuckerberg%20wanted%20Instagram%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20public%20figures%20(like%20influencers)%20and%20video%2C%20and%20think%20about%20competing%20more%20seriously%20with%20YouTube%2C%20according%20to%20a%202018%20exchange%20between%20him%20and%20Mosseri.%20Four%20years%20later%2C%20Zuckerberg%20would%20have%20a%20similar%20conversation%20with%20Alison.%20%26quot%3BDifferentiating%20between%20IG%20and%20FB%20is%20important%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20find%20a%20strategy%20that%20doesn't%20leave%20one%20service%20picking%20up%20the%20scraps%20the%20other%20service%20leaves%20behind%20or%20having%20either%20service%20artificially%20or%20unreasonably%20constrain%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20to%20Alison%20in%20a%202022%20email%20thread.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adam%20Mosseri%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Instagram%2C%20testifies%20during%20the%20Senate%20Commerce%2C%20Science%20and%20Transportation%20Subcommittee%20on%20Consumer%20Protection%2C%20Product%20Safety%2C%20and%20Data%20Security%20Committee%20hearing%20titled%20Protecting%20Kids%20Online%3A%20Instagram%20and%20Reforms%20for%20Young%20Users%2C%20in%20Russell%20Building%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20December%208%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661066cb1caec1275a6d7ab1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdam%20Mosseri%20became%20head%20of%20Instagram%20in%202018.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dc0f906a-0fac-4fa2-b8c3-db57cfc55e9a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20drama%20wasn't%20just%20between%20the%20apps%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20documents%20also%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20mounting%20tension%20between%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Instagram's%20cofounders%2C%20Kevin%20Systrom%20and%20Mike%20Krieger%2C%20in%20the%20months%20before%20their%20ultimate%20departure%20from%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg's%20May%202018%20email%20to%20executives%20reveals%20concerns%20around%20retaining%20Systrom%20and%20Kreiger%20at%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithin%20our%20current%20discussion%20framework%20where%20we%20have%20to%20tread%20very%20carefully%20when%20discussing%20any%20possible%20downsides%20of%20promoting%20Instagram%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20how%20we'll%20even%20articulate%20the%20decisions%20I'm%20suggesting%20here%20to%20Kevin%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20the%20email%2C%20Zuckerberg%20describes%20Systrom%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20excellent%20product%20leader%20who%20has%20built%20something%20massively%20successful%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20team%20player.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20by%20the%20very%20fact%20of%20him%20pushing%20so%20hard%20for%20what%20he%20believes%20is%20right%20and%20our%20desire%20to%20retain%20him%2C%20we%20compromise%20more%20than%20we%20would%20for%20almost%20any%20other%20leader%2C%20and%20over%20time%20those%20compromises%20compound%20to%20creating%20a%20large%20imbalance%20in%20the%20value%20flows%20between%20the%20apps%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kevin%20Systrom%2C%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20Instagram%2C%20prepares%20for%20Wednesday's%20announcement%20about%20IGTV%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20June%2019%2C%202018%2C.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68068f2c3fe8d39283639f36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInstagram%20cofounder%20Kevin%20Systrom%20left%20the%20company%20in%202018.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJeff%20Chiu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%2C%20Mosseri%20and%20Zuckerberg%20also%20discussed%20Systrom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20caught%20up%20with%20Kevin%20briefly%20last%20night%20but%20it's%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20get%20a%20read%20on%20what's%20going%20on%20as%20the%20relationship%20is%20strained%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosseri%20said%20in%20a%20June%202018%20email%20to%20Zuckerberg%20about%20shifting%20Instagram's%20priorities.%20In%20August%2C%20Mosseri%20told%20Zuckerberg%20that%20Systrom%20and%20Krieger%20%26quot%3Bseem%20to%20be%20struggling%20with%20all%20of%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20September%2C%20both%20Systrom%20and%20Krieger%20stepped%20down%20from%20Instagram%2C%20with%20Mosseri%20taking%20over%20as%20head%20of%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%2