rvice%20that%20offers%20members%20money%20back%20on%20Uber%20rides%20and%20discounts%20on%20food%20deliveries%2C%20among%20other%20things%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Uber%20has%20touted%20the%20subscription%2C%20which%20costs%20%249.99%20a%20month%20or%20%2496%20a%20year%2C%20as%20a%20way%20to%20get%20customers%20to%20make%20return%20purchases%20on%20its%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20pitching%20Uber%20One%20to%20consumers%2C%20Uber%20overpromises%20how%20much%20users%20could%20save%2C%20the%20FTC%20said%20in%20its%20complaint.%20Uber%20also%20signed%20some%20users%20up%20for%20the%20subscription%20without%20their%20knowledge%2C%20and%20makes%20it%20tricky%20to%20cancel%2C%20the%20FTC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2025%2F04%2Fftc-takes-action-against-uber-deceptive-billing-cancellation-practices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmericans%20are%20tired%20of%20getting%20signed%20up%20for%20unwanted%20subscriptions%20that%20seem%20impossible%20to%20cancel%2C%26quot%3B%20FTC%20Chairman%20Andrew%20Ferguson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Uber%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bdisappointed%20that%20the%20FTC%20chose%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20this%20action%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20Uber%20believes%20it%20will%20prevail%20in%20an%20anticipated%20court%20battle%20with%20the%20FTC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUber%20One's%20sign-up%20and%20cancellation%20processes%20are%20clear%2C%20simple%2C%20and%20follow%20the%20letter%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BUber%20does%20not%20sign%20up%20or%20charge%20consumers%20without%20their%20consent%2C%20and%20cancellations%20can%20now%20be%20done%20anytime%20in-app%20and%20take%20most%20people%2020%20seconds%20or%20less.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC's%20lawsuit%20says%20that%20Uber%20promises%20users%20%2425%20a%20month%20in%20savings%20if%20they%20use%20Uber%20One.%20That%20figure%20doesn't%20include%20what%20users%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20subscription%2C%20the%20FTC%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20also%20cites%20users%20who%20%26quot%3Bsay%20they%20were%20enrolled%20without%20consent%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20FTC%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20user%20cited%20in%20the%20FTC's%20complaint%20said%20that%20they%20clicked%20%26quot%3Bexit%2C%20reject%2C%20deny%26quot%3B%20every%20time%20Uber%20asked%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20Uber%20One%20when%20they%20created%20their%20Uber%20account.%20Later%2C%20when%20they%20checked%20their%20bank%20account%20activity%2C%20they%20realized%20that%20Uber%20had%20actually%20signed%20them%20up%20for%20the%20subscription%20service%2C%20according%20to%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20charged%20a%20different%20person%20%249.99%20a%20month%20for%20Uber%20One%2C%20though%20that%20person%20never%20had%20an%20Uber%20account%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fftc_gov%2Fpdf%2Fuberonecomplaint.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC's%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20even%20know%20how%20they%20got%20my%20debit%20card%20info%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20unnamed%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20about%20Uber%20or%20a%20similar%20app%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-signed-users-up-uber-one-subscription-without-consent-ftc-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745261130000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68068526a466d2b74ab3b61f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-signed-users-up-uber-one-subscription-without-consent-ftc-2025-4%22%